    "body": "### Problem\n\nI was experimenting with the new `update` option in `vim.api.nvim_set_hl` and tried updating a hlgroup that was previously linked. It worked, but `:hi` shows incomplete info.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean`\n\n1. `50o<Esc>`\n2. `set nu`\n3. `:lua vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, \"RedBG\", { bg = \"red\" })`\n4. `:lua vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, \"LineNr\", { link = \"RedBG\" })`\n5. `lua vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, \"LineNr\", { fg = \"green\", update = true })`\n\nBefore the last step:\n\n<img width=\"352\" height=\"141\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/03f48638-3f19-4c1d-8ceb-dac1793c8938\" />\n\nAfter the last step:\n\n<img width=\"352\" height=\"141\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f80b3717-0b83-41b4-9e0f-6a4df9c754c7\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nLine numbers are updated, but the information about where the red bg is from is lost, I would expect either `links to RedGB` or `guibg=red` in the output.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-65+gb346b87fb2-Homebrew\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.3.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nwezterm\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
